# ============================================================================
# Development Environment Variables
# ============================================================================
# These variables are used when running the development server (npm run dev)
# The Vite dev server will proxy API and WebSocket requests to the backend

# API URL for local development
# This should match your local backend server
VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:8000

# WebSocket URL for local development
# This should match your local backend WebSocket endpoint
VITE_WS_URL=ws://localhost:8000/ws/notifications

# ============================================================================
# Note: Vite Proxy Configuration
# ============================================================================
# The vite.config.ts includes proxy configuration that forwards:
# - /api/* requests to http://localhost:8000/api/*
# - /ws/* requests to ws://localhost:8000/ws/*
#
# This means you can also use relative URLs in development:
# - fetch('/api/health') instead of fetch('http://localhost:8000/api/health')
# - new WebSocket('/ws/notifications') instead of new WebSocket('ws://localhost:8000/ws/notifications')
#
# However, using full URLs (as configured above) is more explicit and works
# in both development and production without code changes.